# 🌐 Multi-Cloud Migration & Parity Assessment
## Current State
- On-prem: vSphere/KVM + RHEL 8/9 + Ubuntu 20.04 + Windows Server 2019
- Network: Local DC routing, static DNS, isolated AD forest
- Compliance: Internal audit only

## Target State (Multi-Cloud Parity)
| Layer                 | AWS                                            | Azure                            | GCP                              | On-Prem/OCI/HCS      |
|--------------         |----------------------                          |----------------------            |----------------------            |----------------------|
| Network               | TGW (ASN 64512)                                | vWAN + ExpressRoute              | Cloud Interconnect (ASN 65001)   | Cisco BGP/OSPF       |
| Compute               | EC2 + EKS nodes                                | VM + AKS nodes                   | GCE + GKE nodes                  | vSphere/KVM clusters |
| Identity              | AWS Managed AD                                 | Azure AD Connect                 | Cloud Identity Sync              | On-prem AD DS        |
| Hardening             | CIS L1 + AWS SSM                               | Azure Policy + Defender          | GCP OSConfig + SCC               | Ansible + Chef       |
| Parity Target         | Same kernel, same CIS, same DNS, same RBAC     | Same                             | Same                             | Same                 |

## Telecom/Enterprise Hybrid Reality Gaps
- Low-latency BGP peering across AWS/Azure/GCP/on-prem
- FinTech payment routing redundancy (PCI-DSS aligned)
- Safaricom ecosystem API gateway placement (low-bandwidth edge)

## Leadership & Process Alignment
- Architecture review cadence: bi-weekly
- Infra/security standards: CIS + internal hardening baseline
- Stakeholder sign-off: Network, Security, Compliance, Finance

## 🌐 Network Parity: BGP + CIDR Blueprint
| Environment | Primary CIDR     | BGP ASN | DNS Strategy      | Interconnect Method     |
|-------------|-----------------|---------|-------------------|--------------------------|
| On-Prem DC  | 192.168.0.0/16  | 65000   | AD-integrated DNS | Cisco BGP to cloud       |
| AWS         | 10.0.0.0/16     | 64512   | Route53 + AD sync | TGW + Direct Connect     |
| Azure       | 10.1.0.0/16     | 65500   | Azure DNS + AD    | vWAN + ExpressRoute      |
| GCP         | 10.2.0.0/16     | 65001   | Cloud DNS + Sync  | Cloud Interconnect       |
| OCI/HCS     | 172.16.0.0/16   | 64999   | Private DNS       | FastConnect / Partner DX |


## 💰 FinOps Parity: Cost-Aware Migration
| Workload Type | On-Prem Monthly | AWS Estimate | Azure Estimate | GCP Estimate     | Optimization Lever           |
|-------------- |-----------------|--------------|----------------|--------------    |-------------------           |
| Dev/Test VMs  | $450            | $320 (Spot)  | $340 (Spot)    | $310 (Preempt)   | Auto-shutdown + Spot         |
| Prod DB       | $1,200          | $980 (RI 1yr)| $1,050 (RI)    | $960 (CUD)       | Reserved Instances           |
| AI/R&D GPU    | $2,500          | $1,800 (Spot)| $1,950 (Spot)  | $1,750 (Preempt) | GPU autoscale + quantization |


## ⚠️ Migration Risk Register
| Risk                          | Impact | Mitigation                                       | Owner             |
|------                         |--------|------------                                      |-------            |
| BGP flapping during cutover   | High   | Pre-test in lab + rollback runbook               | Network Lead      |
| AD sync latency > 5min        | Medium | Async queue + local cache fallback               | Identity Engineer |
| CIS drift post-migration      | High   | Automated drift detection + Ansible remediation  | DevSecOps         |
| Cost overrun in first 90 days | Medium | FinOps dashboard + budget alerts + weekly review | Cloud Eng Lead    |


